reviews.title: never again.
reviews.text:
Too expensive for what was offered, everything for extra pay and the portions are still small, fried potatoes dripping with fat, fries looked like chips, all small pieces, piece of meat was for a child etc. etc.
Staff very brutal if you say anything.

tips.body: Beter een all you can eat in het plaatsje zelf bezoeken, stukker goedkoper en nog beter ook!

reviews.title: Hotel in beautiful surroundings for 1 night
reviews.text:
Hotel is located in a beautiful location on the Veluwe, staff and service are good. The hotel itself is a bit stuck in time, old-fashioned and 'dusty'. Old carpet, crappy furniture, etc. No USB connection in the room, no coffee/tea facilities in the room. Very small rooms. Everything outdated, rust on heating. Burn hole in net curtains. We chose this hotel because of the wellness and swimming pool. For wellness you pay €15 pp per hour!! Just ridiculous. Should be free in a hotel in our opinion.
Bed, room and bathroom were clean. No comment about that. Ate dinner in the evening. Was good food and enough. Breakfast of €15 was disappointing for that price. Too little choice. Buffet too small. Would not recommend this hotel to my family and friends.

reviews.title: A little expensive but good food
reviews.text: Took a while to get served. It was busy but most people were served quickly. The manager seated us quickly and got us menus and took our drinks order... then forgot about us! We had to ask other staff to get our drinks. Again, it took a while to have our food order taken, two other tables who arrived later got their order taken before us. But when we did order, the food arrived quicker than expected and was very good.

reviews.title: Good food made up for lesser reception
reviews.text:
Restaurant within the Princess Hotel.
Although we made a reservation, there was no table available. Staff wasn't quite sure what to to with this situation and offered a table in a corner, away from other guests. Maybe because of this, but staff seemed to be overly friendly.
The restaurant offers a not overly extensive but good menu. 
Mustard soup with crispy bacon, skin baked salmon fillet with choron sauce and fried capers, hazelnut parfait with vanilla sauce and Bastonge cookies crumble, all delicious. The various courses were served right on time and well sized.

articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

tripContent.title: 11 stops that prove Louisville is a cultural hub
tripContent.description: Louisville is brimming with rich history, art of all kinds, and architecture that's not to be missed. Check out these must-stop cultural attractions in Kentucky's biggest city.

tripContent.title: Chase horizons and conquer trails across Nevada’s rugged backcountry
tripContent.description: Nevada’s wild places were made for those who move at their own pace. Wander through desert canyons, alpine lakes, and ancient rock formations, all in one trip. Whether you're chasing stars in a dark sky park or breathing deep in the high mountains, this is the untamed side of the Silver State, ready to be roamed, hiked, and discovered.

tripContent.title: Santa Fe: heritage & history on the Original Route 66
tripContent.description: Looking for adventure on the original Route 66? Santa Fe, the oldest state capital, is a must-stop for history buffs. The city, founded in 1610, is older than the United States—but the area has been populated for well over a thousand years. With so much history and heritage, you'll want to allow plenty of time to explore the best of the Southwest—so here are 12 suggestions for things to see, do, and learn.

tripContent.title: Discover Louisville’s global cuisine at these hidden gems
tripContent.description: When it comes to your taste buds, Louisville’s lively food scene invites you to adventure beyond city limits. Plan your culinary exploration with this roundup of the city’s most-loved eateries, serving classic and creative dishes inspired by food and festivities from around the world.
